Package <Unnamed>

Class Summary
ConstantStrings This class contains some static string constants that are used throughout the program.
DataCube This class represents a three dimensional set of double values (think of it as a cube).
DataLoader DataLoader contains two methods to load data from a DataSet into a GlyphTable.
DataSet This is the superclass for the classes DataMatrix and DataCube.
DataTable This class represents a two dimensional table of double values.
GlyphTable One of the central classes of the program.
Layouts This class contains only static methods that will compute a specific layout like a Morton Z-Curve for a set of items.
MenuAction This implementation of an ActionListener gets active if a menu or something else in the PixelFrame has been activated.
PixelFrame The PixelFrame holds the whole visualization.
PixelRenderer The PixelRenderer draws the items onto the screen and also calculates their borders.
PixelSelector This class triggers events after actions like dragging an item or just moving the mouse.
Sort Currently not in use.
TestCube Implementation of a DataCube for testing purposes.
TestTable Implementation of a DataTable for testing purposes.
VisuMain The main class of the program.
ZoomControler The Zoom Controller zooms the display and resizes it if the mouse wheel is used.
